orpse of the now-deceased [[General Zod]] also appears in the film in a crucial role, however, [[Michael Shannon]] did not film any scenes for the film and his corpse was created using the physique of fitness model [[Greg Plitt]] and a head-shot of Shannon.<ref>{{cite video|title=BATMAN VS SUPERMAN Zod Body BTS ADI|author=studioADI|publisher=YouTube|date=April 2, 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QdRTQDXxdYY}}</ref>\n\n===Non-recurring characters===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n'''''Superman'''''\n*1st Elder \u2013 [[Trevor Howard]]\n*2nd Elder \u2013 [[Harry Andrews]]\n*Vond-Ah \u2013 [[Maria Schell]]\n\n'''''Superman II'''''\n*Sheriff \u2013 [[Clifton James]]\n\n'''''Superman III'''''\n*Gus Gorman \u2013 [[Richard Pryor]]\n*Lorelei \u2013 [[Pamela Stephenson]]\n*Ross Webster \u2013 [[Robert Vaughn]]\n*Vera Webster \u2013 [[Annie Ross]]\n{{col-break}}\n\n'''''Superman IV: The Quest for Peace'''''\n*David Warfield \u2013 [[Sam Wanamaker]]\n*Harry Howler \u2013 [[William Hootkins]]\n*Jean Pierre Dubois \u2013 [[Jim Broadbent]]\n*Lacy Warfield \u2013 [[Mariel Hemingway]]\n*Lenny Luthor \u2013 [[Jon Cryer]]\n*Nuclear Man \u2013 [[Mark Pillow]]\n\n'''''Superman Returns'''''\n*Jason White \u2013 [[Tristan Lake Leabu]]\n*Kitty Kowalski \u2013 [[Parker Posey]]\n*Richard White \u2013 [[James Marsden]]\n*Stanford \u2013 [[Kal Penn]]\n{{col-break}}\n\n'''''Man of Steel'''''\n*Colonel Nathan Hardy \u2013 [[Christopher Meloni]]\n*[[Emil Hamilton|Dr. Emil Hamilton]] \u2013 [[Richard Schiff]]\n*[[Faora]] \u2013 [[Antje Traue]]\n*Tor-An \u2013 Richard Cetrone\n*Jed Eubanks \u2013 [[Tahmoh Penikett]]\n*Sergeant Sedowsky \u2013 [[Alessandro Juliani]]\n*[[Steve Lombard]] \u2013 [[Michael Kelly (American actor)|Michael Kelly]]\n*[[Whitney Fordman]] \u2013 Robert Gerdisch\n\n'''''Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice'''''\n*June Finch \u2013 [[Holly Hunter]]\n*[[Mercy Graves]] \u2013 [[Tao Okamoto]]\n*[[Doomsday (DC Comics)|Doomsday]] - [[Robin Atkin Downes]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Box office performance===\n{{dagger}} indicates that the film in the series is currently playing\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Film\n! colspan=\"2\" | Release date\n! colspan=\"4\" | Box office gross\n! rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|{{Abbr|Ref(s)|References}}}}\n|-\n! North America\n! Other<br />territories\n! North America\n! North American<br />gross when adjusted<br />for inflation\n! Other<br />territories\n! Worldwide\n|-\n| ''[[Superman (1978 film)|Superman]]''\n| colspan=2| <div style=\"text-align: center;\">December 15, 1978</div>\n| $134,218,018\n| ${{formatnum:{{Inflation|US|134218018|1978}}}}\n| $166&nbsp;million\n| $300,218,018\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=superman.htm | title=Superman (1978) | work=[[Box Office Mojo]] | accessdate=2007-05-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Superman II]]''\n| June 19, 1981\n| December 4, 1980\n| $108,185,706\n| ${{formatnum:{{Inflation|US|108185706|1980}}}}\n| $82.2&nbsp;million\n| $190,385,706\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=superman2.htm | title=Superman II (1981) | work=[[Box Office Mojo]] | accessdate=2007-05-17}}</ref><ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite book|last1=Block|first1=Alex Ben|last2=Wilson|first2=Lucy Autrey|last3=Lucas|first3=George|last4=Coppola|first4=Francis Ford|title=George Lucas's Blockbusting: A Decade-by-Decade Survey of Timeless Movies Including Untold Secrets of Their Financial and Cultural Success|date=2010|publisher=itBooks|location=New York|isbn=9780061778896|pages=vii & 534|edition=1st|url=https://archive.org/details/georgelucassbloc00alex}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Superman III]]''\n| colspan=2| <div style=\"text-align: center;\">June 17, 1983</div>\n| $59,950,623\n| ${{formatnum:{{Inflation|US|59950623|1983}}}}\n| $20.2&nbsp;million\n| $80,150,623\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxoff